Date: 0/0/1870
Source: TrNZI
Author:
Vol / Page: 3/63
Edition:
Quote:  [Attene albifacies, wekau of the Maoris, is known by some up-country settlers as the big owl or <i> laughing-jackass </i>.] Why it should share with one of our petrels and the great Dacelo of Australia the trivial name of `laughing jackass` we know not; if its cry resembles laughter at all it is the uncontrollable outburst, the convulsive shout of insanity.
Notes: T.H. Potts

